President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring December 17th as Wright Brothers Day. This day commemorates the historic achievement of Wilbur and Orville Wright, who successfully flew their airplane for 12 seconds on December 17, 1903. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of innovation and highlights the need to improve education in science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM) fields. It also recognizes the contributions of Katharine Wright, the sister of the Wright brothers, who supported their aviation enterprise and played a significant role in its success. The proclamation concludes by urging all Americans to draw inspiration from the Wright family's dedication to bold ideas and scientific thinking.